Surprise.com is on a mission to turn the magical, uplifting experience of Surprise into a daily, weekly, and monthly life event – because it makes people happy. Our Surprise Box, and delightful companion app, is the most exciting way to get amazing goodies from brands you love and brands you’re about to love. With daily games, the ability to send and get Surprises from friends, and Grand Surprises – every day is filled with wow!
 We're now looking for an experienced and motivated analytics leader to join our data team – the backbone of our data-driven operations – and architect our internal data infrastructure. You'll partner with company leadership to implement and measure the impact of strategic projects and inform how our engineers build the next generation of data platforms. Our ideal candidate maintains a deep systems background and will use that competence to guide the team towards well-engineered and durable solutions.
 Your internal customers will span every team at Surprise, and your leadership, talent, and commitment to technical excellence will make a tremendous impact day in and day out – if this challenge excites you, apply below.
 What will you be doing?

Researching, designing, and implementing machine learning algorithms;
Communicating results, technical constraints, and decisions to the business and non-specialists;
Delivering rapid prototypes and proof of concepts that demonstrate real value;
Creating and delivering progress reports, slide decks, proposals, and documentation.

What are we looking for?

Upper-Intermediate English (B2) or higher;
A BS or higher in computer science or a related field;
4+ years of experience in software development;
2+ years of experience in Data Science;
Extensive knowledge of and practical experience in Machine Learning, Recommender Systems, and Algorithms;
Understanding of Machine Learning techniques like Linear Regression, Decision Trees, Collaborative Filtering, Anomaly Detection, etc.;
Practical experience with high-level programming language like Python and DS frameworks;
Proficiency in database query languages such as SQL;
Understanding of the ETL process;
Knowledge of Linear Algebra, Probability and Statistics, and Numerical methods;
Understanding of software development process, Agile approach, and CI/CD.

What skills will come in handy?

Experience building large-scale recommender engines (collaborative filtering, KNN, associative rule learning, custom similarity metrics, etc.);
Understanding of predictive analytics (time-series analysis and forecasting, survival and duration analysis, etc.);
Ability to apply graph analysis techniques for structural pattern recognition;
Applied statistics skills, such as distributions, hypothesis testing, regression analysis, etc.;
Experience building microservices and containerized applications (Docker, k8s);
Familiarity with Big Data frameworks — Hadoop, Spark Experience with Natural Language Processing NoSQL databases, such as MongoDB, Cassandra, HBase;
Experience with mining of structured, semi-structured, and unstructured data;
Experience with data visualization tools, such as Ggplot2, Plotly, Matplotlib.

Benefits

Work on interesting and challenging projects, while building a pioneering software category;
Great atmosphere, with the vibe and energy of a high-growth tech company;
Competitive compensation package;
Paid time off and Public Holidays;
Close collaboration between international team members;
And, of course, we use Surprise internally!

We are looking for an IT Business Analyst for our Product team. Product Management in Rubrikk Group is not inscribed in stone. We are all curious and continuously learning what our millions of users and customers want. We have a product portfolio that includes both features on websites and products for customers. We hope you can bring your own ideas on how to ensure that we pursue the right products.
 As an IT Business Analyst you discuss with the stakeholders and subject matter experts, writing up requirements, assumptions, limitations and acceptance criteria. You work with the development teams for product refinements and support the development team during development with continuous clarifications, and decide upon how the functionality in the product must work. 
The ideal candidate is a solid and proven professional. You have a keen eye for details and are willing to learn and progress in your professional evolution. You have a proven track record in a similar setting, where you have been working end-to-end on research and data analysis, synthesising the findings in crisp documents, communicating with stakeholders and seeing things through to execution. 
The position reports to the Head of Product.
 Your mission:

You will be in the intersection with teams of developers, data scientists, UX/UI designers and more.
You will drive the discovery, refinement, prioritisation and development of new features and products.
You will gather insights, feedback and problems from our customers and users around the world and convert these into delightful digital product experiences.
Work closely with the Sales and Business Operation teams to ensure the product roadmap is aligned and keep everyone informed and excited about the direction the product is heading.
Make sure that our product development is supported by data, using Google Analytics to measure impact of new feature, and uncovering potential for improvement within existing products.
Create and maintain relationships in the relevant industries allowing you to know what is happening on the ground, being able to anticipate how products would do and bounce off ideas on potential customers and users.


 We expect you to bring:

 3+ years of experience within consultancy, analyst, software testing/development;
Demonstrable understanding of web technology; 
Experience in web applications analysis; 
Strong English communication skills (language used within the company); 
Strong client-facing and teamwork skills; 
Structured, organised, detail oriented; 
Capacity to motivate others; 
Ability to work under pressure on multiple projects within your project timeframes; 
Extensive experience within data analytics, such as data modelling, Tableau, Google analytics, etc. 


Nice to have:
 Experience working with these tools or similar is a plus:

 Google Analytics;
Google Search Console;
Figma;
Sketch;
Python;
Database query.


 What we offer you:
 We would like you to have a meaningful experience, and possibly to grow as we grow, and learn as we learn. We believe in fairness and transparency, and sharing a common goal, while we enjoy the journey.
 Here, you will find:

 A modern and international environment, with a Nordic mindset, fairness and open mind.
Flexible working schedule. Flexible means: Monday to Friday, you can start anytime between 8am to 10am, and work 8 hours per day. 30 minutes lunch break is included, so effective working time is 7.5 hours.
Continuous support, and training as needed.
Private medical insurance.
Social events.

